<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Brownish ochraceous with brown markings. Crown with two spots on either side of median line, one lateral spot and thin marginal band on pronotum, basal triangles of mesoscutum brown; oblique band traversing pro- and mesopleura, anterior and posterior broad areas of metapleura, shining dark brown. Forewing veins interrupted by ochraceous spots. Frontoclypeus with darker shade of brown laterally. Bases of hind femoral apical setae dark brown, bases of tibial setae brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Crown with anterior margin slightly produced medially beyond compound eyes and more or less conically rounded. Pronotum almost three times wider than the length, combined length of head and pronotum almost equal to combined length of mesoscutum and scutellum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
Male pygofer abruptly narrowed postero-dorsally, ventral process elongate blade-like with prominent teeth on ventral margin, sclerotized process along dorsal margin, curved mesally and acuminate (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1372,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[208,1351,202,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[199,1368,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 39. Mahellus cardoni sp. nov., male genitalia. 32. Abdominal segment VIII and genital capsule, lateral view; 33. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 34. Connective, dorsal view; 35. Style, dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 38, Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 39. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569769/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 32–33</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1424,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 52" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,432,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,419,1713]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 52. Speceis of Mahellus. 48. Chaetotaxy of forefemur of M. distanti; 49. Chaetotaxy of metabasitarsus and second tarsomete of M. distanti, ventral view; 50 – 52. Posterior portion of male pygofer of Mahellus, dorsal view showing dorsal marginal sclerotized process: 50. M. cardoni sp. nov.; 51. M. distanti; 52. M. ungulatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569771/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">50</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate elongate (8.5 times as long as width at midlength), more or less of uniform width, apex rounded, without spine-like projection (
<figureCitation box="[507,597,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[208,1351,202,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[199,1368,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 39. Mahellus cardoni sp. nov., male genitalia. 32. Abdominal segment VIII and genital capsule, lateral view; 33. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 34. Connective, dorsal view; 35. Style, dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 38, Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 39. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569769/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped with median longitudinal apodeme, stem short. Dorsal connective membranous, unpigmented band-like. Style slender, apical half of apophysis produced into thin process (
<figureCitation box="[252,336,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[208,1351,202,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[199,1368,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 39. Mahellus cardoni sp. nov., male genitalia. 32. Abdominal segment VIII and genital capsule, lateral view; 33. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 34. Connective, dorsal view; 35. Style, dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 38, Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 39. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569769/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft tubular and basal 1/3 lamellated, dorsal and lateral subapical processes more or less of same length; lateral process spinose apically, dorsal process spinose along inner margin and distal margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,286,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[208,1351,202,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[199,1368,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 39. Mahellus cardoni sp. nov., male genitalia. 32. Abdominal segment VIII and genital capsule, lateral view; 33. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 34. Connective, dorsal view; 35. Style, dorsal view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 38, Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 39. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569769/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 37–39</figureCitation>
).Segment X in lateral aspect longer than broad, with flat ventral surface, in dorsal aspect broad at base and slightly narrowed distally, without ventral process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,870,895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 6.4 and 
<quantity box="[548,636,870,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
long, head 
<quantity box="[771,858,870,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes and 1.8 and 2.0 mm wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
