<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,1255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName box="[199,322,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardoni">
<emphasis box="[199,322,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. cardoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[449,740,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Jassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="determinatus">
<emphasis box="[449,632,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. determinatus</emphasis>
(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[808,928,1122,1147]" name="Seychelles" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
in having similar male genitalia. However, it differs from the latter in the following characters (characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1066,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Jassus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="determinatus">
<emphasis box="[881,1066,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">M. determinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parenthesis): subgenital plate more or less of uniform width throughout with apex rounded (of uneven width and apex truncate); the style with apical half abruptly narrowed into thin process (apical 1/4 gradually narrowed).
</paragraph>
